# ── DENY-BY-DEFAULT ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This public repo is built from an explicit allowlist (see MANIFEST.md):
# ignore everything, then re-allow only vetted, secret-scanned paths. This
# bounds the irreversible risk of leaking a secret into public git history.

# 1) ignore everything
*

# 2) re-allow the vetted tree
!.gitignore
!LICENSE
!README.md
!requirements.txt
!MANIFEST.md

!quant_lab/
!quant_lab/__init__.py
!quant_lab/validation/
!quant_lab/validation/__init__.py
!quant_lab/validation/dsr.py
!quant_lab/validation/kill_tests.py
!quant_lab/validation/engine.py
!quant_lab/validation/explanation.py
!quant_lab/validation/spec.py

!tests/
!tests/test_dsr.py
!tests/test_verdict_user_layer.py

!docs/
!docs/DESIGN.md
!docs/DSR.md
!docs/VERDICT.md
!docs/example_verdict_whalefollow_v3.md

# 3) hard belt-and-suspenders: never track these even if re-added above
trial_counter.json
*.sqlite
*.duckdb
*.log
.env
**/data/
**/secrets*
**/*credential*
**/.DS_Store
__pycache__/
*.pyc
_*.txt
